[assistant] Fixed the VM startup failure by changing the Security Manager JVM option to be conditional.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.bytebuddy/byte-buddy-agent/1.12.4/build.gradle`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed from unconditional:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```groovy
[assistant] tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {
[assistant]     systemProperty "java.security.manager", "allow"
[assistant] }
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] to:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```groovy
[assistant] tasks.named("test") {
[assistant]     if ((JavaVersion.current().majorVersion as int) < 24) {
[assistant]         jvmArgs += ["-Djava.security.manager=allow"]
[assistant]     }
[assistant] }
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] This avoids passing `-Djava.security.manager=allow` on JDK 24+ / JDK 25, where enabling or allowing the Security Manager is no longer supported and causes VM initialization to fail.
[assistant] 
[assistant] The `InstallerTest` already catches `UnsupportedOperationException` from `System.setSecurityManager(...)`, so it should now pass on JDK 25 while still exercising the security-manager branch on older JDKs that support it. Tests were not run.
